<p>I am using <a href="https://github.com/clojure-liberator/liberator/" rel="nofollow">liberator</a> to build a API using Clojure. Given the follow code:</p>  <pre><code>(defresource single-customer [id]   :allowed-methods [:get, :put]   :exists? (fn [_]              (let [e (get @cust/customers (keyword id))]                (if-not (nil? e)                  {::entry e})))   :existed? (fn [_] (nil? (get @cust/customers (keyword id) ::sentinel)))   :available-media-types ["application/json"]   :can-put-to-missing? false   :put! (fn [q] (cust/set-as-fraudulent id))   :handle-ok ::entry) </code></pre>  <p>Someone when can tell me if is possible, like the GET request, when I send a PUT request it be redirected to the resource ? <code>"/customer/1"</code> (for example) ?</p>